# âœ… Business Continuity Planning (BCP) Checklist for Cybersecurity Incident Recovery

This checklist supports recovery efforts after a cybersecurity incident by aligning business operations with IT recovery actions and organizational continuity goals.

---

## ðŸ”¹ 1. Governance & Documentation
- [ ] Confirm BCP policy is approved and aligned with organizational objectives  
- [ ] Ensure roles and responsibilities are clearly defined  
- [ ] Review business impact analysis (BIA) to validate critical business functions  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 2. Incident Impact Assessment
- [ ] Evaluate which business processes and systems are affected  
- [ ] Map affected assets to critical business functions (from BIA)  
- [ ] Estimate financial, operational, and reputational impact  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 3. Alternative Operations Planning
- [ ] Identify backup systems, sites, or cloud-based environments  
- [ ] Document and test manual workarounds or alternative workflows  
- [ ] Ensure remote work capabilities are functional (if applicable)  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 4. IT & Data Recovery Coordination
- [ ] Ensure Recovery Time Objective (RTO) and Recovery Point Objective (RPO) are met  
- [ ] Coordinate with IT Disaster Recovery Plan (DRP) for reimaging, restoration, patching  
- [ ] Verify data integrity after restoration from backups  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 5. Communication Plan Execution
- [ ] Notify internal teams using predefined contact lists  
- [ ] Inform external stakeholders (customers, partners, regulators) as needed  
- [ ] Use pre-approved communication templates for speed and accuracy  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 6. Regulatory & Legal Compliance
- [ ] Report the incident to relevant authorities if required (e.g., breach notification laws)  
- [ ] Document recovery actions for audit purposes  
- [ ] Preserve digital evidence for legal or forensic follow-up  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 7. Post-Recovery Validation
- [ ] Conduct system and user acceptance testing (UAT)  
- [ ] Monitor for re-infection or residual threats  
- [ ] Resume normal operations based on formal approval  

---

## ðŸ”¹ 8. Review & Update
- [ ] Perform post-incident review and root cause analysis  
- [ ] Update the BCP, DRP, and IRP based on lessons learned  
- [ ] Schedule tabletop exercises to test revised plans  

---

> **Tip:** Integrate this checklist into your BCP documentation repository, version-control it, and include references to applicable frameworks (e.g., ISO 22301, NIST SP 800-34, SOC 2 CC7.2).
